{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-js","path":"/blog/starcode","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Following the <a href=\"https://huggingface.co/blog/starchat-alpha\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">tutorial</a> and <a href=\"https://huggingface.co/blog/codeparrot\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">this</a>. For optimization <a href=\"https://github.com/huggingface/peft\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">PEFT</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Install <a href=\"https://docs.conda.io/en/latest/miniconda.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">miniconda</a></li>\n<li>Start Anaconda in your terminal. For example, open <a href=\"/science/how-to-run-dalle-locally\">Alacritty</a> and run <code class=\"language-text\">C:\\Users\\neupo\\miniconda3\\Scripts\\activate.bat</code>. Also see <a href=\"/code/anaconda-in-vscode-terminal\">VS Code example</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">conda create <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-n</span> starchat <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">python</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token number\">3.10</span>\nconda activate starchat\n\n<span class=\"token function\">git</span> clone https://github.com/bigcode-project/starcoder.git\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">cd</span> starcoder/chat\npip <span class=\"token function\">install</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-r</span> requirements.txt</code></pre></div>\n<p>To exit the environment type</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">conda deactivate</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"create-dataset\" style=\"position:relative;\">Create dataset<a href=\"#create-dataset\" aria-label=\"create dataset permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" versio